 086:     ----------
 087:     seed : {None, int, array_like[uint], SeedSequence}, optional

 104:     q : int, optional

 109:         provided uses the default values for the selected size listed in Notes.

 128:     -----
 129:     The JSF generator uses a 4-element state of unsigned integers, either
 130:     uint32 or uint64, a, b, c and d ([1]_). The generator also depends on
 131:     3 parameters p, q, and r that must be between 0 and size-1.
 132:

 134: 
 135:     .. code-block:: python
 136: 
 137:       e = a - ROTL(b, p)
 138:       a = b ^ ROTL(c, q)
 139:       b = c + ROTL(d, r)
 140:       c = d + e
 141:       d = e + a
 142: 
 143:     where d is the value returned at the end of a single iteration and
 144:     ROTL(x, y) left rotates x by y bits.
 145:

 147:

 149:

 151:      Parameter          32       64
 152:     =========== === ========= ==========
 153:         p               27        7
 154:         q               17       13
 155:         r               0        37
 156:     =========== === ========= ==========

 159:     ``JSF.parameters`` for a list of the values provided by Jenkins. Note
 160:     that if ``r`` is 0, the generator uses only 2 rotations.
 161: 
 162:     **State and Seeding**
 163: 
 164:     The state consists of the 4 values a, b, c and d. The size of these values
 165:     depends on ``size``. The seed value is an unsided integer with the same

 167:
